Established: May 14, 1930
Carlsbad Caverns has 117 caves, the longest of which is over 120 miles (190 km) long. The Big
Room is almost 4,000 feet (1,200 m) long, and the caves are home to over 400,000 Mexican
free-tailed bats and sixteen other species. Above ground are the Chihuahuan Desert and
Rattlesnake Springs.
